d into England both in the reign of Edward the Confessor and by the Normans (in the forms <i>Walt(i)er</i>, <i>Waut(i)er</i>). After the Norman Conquest it soon became one of the most popular personal names in Britain. Compare   Walther  .","Germanized or Americanized form of Czech, Slovak, Croatian, and Slovenian <b>Valter</b> and Czech <b>Valtr</b>: from the personal name <i>Valter</i>, <i>Valtr</i>, of ancient Germanic origin (see 1 above)."],"variants":[{"name":"Walthers","meanings":["German: patronymic from the personal name <i>Walther</i> (see   Walter  )."]},{"name":"McQuate","meanings":["Scottish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Uait</b> ‘son of <i>Uat</i>’, Gaelic form of the personal name <i>Wat</i>, a short form of   Walter  . Compare the Irish form   McQuaid  ."]},{"name":"Waltke","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Jurgen, Wilhelmina.","German: from a pet form of any of the ancient Germanic personal names formed with Old High German <i>waltan</i> ‘to rule’ as the first element, as in   Walter  ."]},{"name":"McWaters","meanings":["Scottish and northern Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Uaitéir</b>, a patronymic from a Gaelicized form of the personal name   Walter  , with excrescent English <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Wahler","meanings":["German:","from the personal name <i>Wol(d)er</i>, Low German form of   Walter  .","habitational name for someone from any of various places called Wahl, Wahle, or Wahlen."]},{"name":"McWalter","meanings":["Irish and Scottish: from Gaelic <b>Mac Uaitéir</b> ‘son of   Walter  ’."]},{"name":"Walters","meanings":["English: variant of   Walter  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>.","German: patronymic from   Walter  ."]},{"name":"McQuaid","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Colum, Nuala.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Uaid</b> ‘son of <i>Uad</i>’, Gaelic form of the personal name <i>Wat</i>, a short form of   Walter  . Compare the Scottish form   McQuate  ."]},{"name":"Walther","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt, Hans, Erwin, Wolfgang, Otto, Gerhard, Gunter, Heinz, Klaus, Konrad, Bernd, Bernhard.","German, Dutch, Swedish, and Danish: variant of   Walter  ."]},{"name":"Lauter","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Ernst, Erwin, Kurt, Sigismund, Wolf.","German: topographic name and habitational name, from a common stream name meaning ‘clear’, from Middle High German <i>hlutra</i>, or from any of the places called Lauter or Lauta (Saxony). This surname is also found in France (Alsace and Lorraine) and some other European countries.","Germanized or Americanized form of Slovenian <b>Lavtar</b> or its Croatized and rare Slovenian variant <b>Lautar</b>: from a dialect variant of the personal name <i>Valter</i> (see   Walter  )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Miss Ferch Gwalter was born about 1159. She had at least 1 daughter with Madoc Ap Cadrod."},"et":{"Abt 1159–":"umbes 1159–Surnud","1157–1211":"1157–1211","1195–Female":"1195–Surnud","1159–Female":"1159–Surnud","about 1195":"umbes 1195","1159":"1159","1157":"1157","1211":"1211","Abt 1159":"umbes 1159","1195":"1195","Glamorgan, Glamorganshire, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales"},"fi":{"Abt 1159–":"noin 1159–Kuollut","1157–1211":"1157–1211","1195–Female":"1195–Kuollut","1159–Female":"1159–Kuollut","about 1195":"noin 1195","1159":"1159","1157":"1157","1211":"1211","Abt 1159":"noin 1159","1195":"1195","Glamorgan, Glamorganshire, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales"},"fr":{"Abt 1159–":"environ 1159–Décédée","1157–1211":"1157–1211","1195–Female":"1195–Décédée","1159–Female":"1159–Décédée","about 1195":"environ 1195","1159":"1159","1157":"1157","1211":"1211","Abt 1159":"environ 1159","1195":"1195","Glamorgan, Glamorganshire, Wales":"Glamorgan, Galles","lifeSummary":"Miss Ferch Gwalter est née environ 1159. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Madoc Ap Cadrod."},"de":{"Abt 1159–":"um 1159–Verstorben","1157–1211":"1157–1211","1195–Female":"1195–Verstorben","1159–Female":"1159–V